Margins

1. margins = space around an element 

example
#file index.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>


<body>


    <h1>My Website</h1>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Hic illum ea, tempora inventore sint, corrupti, officia sed beatae aut qui illo provident repudiandae voluptas at dolor. A perferendis recusandae laboriosam.</p>
 
    <div class="box" id="box1">box1</div>
    <div class="box" id="box2">box2</div>
</body>
</html>

body{
    margin: 0px;
}


.box{
    border: 5px solid;
    font-size: 3em;
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
}
   
#box1{
    background-color: red;
    /* margin-top: 50px; */
    /* margin-bottom: 50px; */
    /* margin-left: 50px; */
    /* margin-right: 50px; */
    /* margin-left: auto;  */
    /* margin-left:auto; box1 will locate at the very left side automatically */
    margin: auto;
    /* box1 will stay in the center of the web browser */
}
   
 #box2{
    background-color: blue;
}
